records.nl_statement: Let $p$ be an odd prime. Show that $a$ is a primitive root modulo $p$ iff $a^{(p-1) / q} \not \equiv 1(p)$ for all prime divisors $q$ of $p-1$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Real
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_4_8 {p : ℕ} {a : ZMod p} (hp : Odd p) (hp' : p.Prime) :
  IsPrimitiveRoot a p ↔ (∀ q : ℕ, q ∣ (p-1) → q.Prime → ¬ a^((p-1)/q) = 1) :=
records.baseline_candidate:
theorem autoformalized_theorem_1421 (p a : ℕ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpa : Odd p) :
  IsPrimitiveRoot a p ↔ (∀ q : ℕ, q ∣ p - 1 → q.Prime → ¬ a ^ ((p - 1) / q) ≡ 1 [MOD p]) := by sorry
records.best_cycle_candidate:

  ∀ q : ℕ, q ∣ (p - 1) → q.Prime → ¬ a ^ ((p - 1) / q) ≡ 1 [MOD p] := by sorry
